g.aria-label: The score is read from left to right, top to bottom. Press your pedal for next cue.It is set to the [PgDn] key by default. For rehearsals, use [a-x] to navigate to a cue. = Gradually transition between actions. = Continue this action for a time, then immediately do next action. = Continue this action = Do these actions immediately, one after the other. = Play this cue (by tapping on the pedal). = Improvise by moving your hands around. The velocity of the motion controls the amplitude of the sound. = Improvise by moving your hands from the center of your chest to either side or up and down. This action should be sparse. = Improvise by cuing sounds above or below your chest These should be fluid motions. = Copy player 0 in a mechanical manner. = Copy player 0 in a fluid manner. = Energy level - indicates the overall energy, as manifested in characteristics such as loudness, speed and timbre. R↓= Move your right hand in the position indicated by the arrow. L↓= Move your left hand in the direction indicated by the arrow. = Improvise with both hands. A continuous stream of notes is played. y-axis controls volume and x-axis controls pitch. = Improvise. Hands together increases volume, hands apart decreases. Height controls timbre.
